summary: [Feature] In Defense of Resasuke: Autism-coding and ableism in Aggretsuko
title: [Feature] In Defense of Resasuke: Autism-coding and ableism in Aggretsuko
body:
I’ve been thinking about Aggretsuko a lot lately, the anime about the quintessential millennial red panda who blows off steam from her oppressive accounting job through Death Metal Karaoke.  Season 2 is supposed to air sometime this year, we had the Christmas Special a few months ago, and the protagonist Retsuko herself was nominated for Best Protagonist at the Crunchyroll Awards.  

People loved the deceptively cute death metal panda. The show’s seemingly simple yet charming premise got me on board as well.

But now I have mixed feelings about it.  There is one problem with this otherwise awesome and even progressive anime that really bothers me, and it has to do with Resasuke.  

Specifically, it has to do with the fact that he is very heavily coded as being on the autism spectrum, and in how the ending of the anime played out.

Read it at Anime Feminist!

question: Aggretsuko for the anime ask
answer:
Yoo thanks for this! 😭 i usually never get asks


haven’t heard of it | absolutely never watching | might watch | currently watching | dropped | hated it | meh | a positive okay | liked it | liked it a lot! | loved it | a favorite (clarification: i watched a few episodes but kinda forgot about it 😭)

don’t watch period | drop if not interested within 2-3 episodes | give it a go, could be your thing | 5 star recommendation (idk what this section is buttt people should really give it a go!!)

fav characters: Fenneko!!

least fav characters: that pig guy ugh

fav relationship: haida and retsuko are just 👌🏼 from what i‘ve seen

fav moment: that one scene where haida‘s on a bed (infirmary? Hospital? Idk) and haida confesses to retsuko or something that was so cute

headcanons/theories: pig guy disappears and retsuko finally finds peace 🙏🏼 or, that‘s at least what i wish for her lmao

unpopular opinion: i personally am not really fond of metal so the show‘s a bit hard to watch for me (hence why i semi-dropped it)

how’d you find it: again, the metal (which is like the main sellin point of the show) isn‘t my thing but the art style is super cute and some of the characters are hella likeable

random thoughts: thanks to this ask i‘m prolly gonna start watching it again so thanks for that 😂
